The article is a letter from former President Barack Obama to the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House and Senate Committees on Appropriations and Armed Services, as well as the Chairmen and Ranking Members of the House Committee on Foreign Affairs and the Senate Committee on Foreign Relations. The letter is regarding the accession of Montenegro to the North Atlantic Treaty. It includes an evaluation of how Montenegro will contribute to the security of the North Atlantic area, an evaluation of Montenegro's eligibility for membership based on NATO and US criteria, an explanation of how Montenegro's invitation would affect the national security interests of the United States, an analysis of the military requirements and costs associated with integrating Montenegro into NATO, a preliminary analysis of the implications for the US defense budget and other budgets, an analysis of Montenegro's ability to meet the financial burdens of NATO membership, and an analysis of Montenegro's potential impact on the military effectiveness of NATO. The report is provided in both classified and unclassified forms.